Merge pull request #135 from holygeek/master

Fix racy read/write on socketHandler.acks

Fix racy read/write on socketHandler.acks

Read/write on socketHandler.acks map is not protected by any locks.
socketHandler.onAck() reads it, while socketHandler.Emit() writes to it.
These two operations could very well be happening at the same time so
guard it with a lock.

Merge pull request #84 from fuel-shea/fix-connect

Fix for issue 59

Fix for issue 59

See: https://github.com/googollee/go-socket.io/issues/59

The socket.io client requires an echoed connect packet,
which is mising from the current code.

NOTE: I believe navneetk's example from Mar 18 2015 shows
a different issue.
fix for #67. It will now close the packet when reading an unknown emit

fixes #48 close the open chanel before waiting for nextReader

When sending Binary data, the socket.io client strips the binary
data from the frame and replaces it with a numbered _placeholder.
Once the placeholder frame is ack'ed the client sends another
frame with the binary data.  Without this fix go-socket.io never
acks the placeholder frame and so waits indefinitely for the data
frame.
Return an error when a socket.emit called with too few arguments (fixes #71)
